<h3>Radiation and Cloudiness</h3>
<br><br>
In March it was less cloudy than normal almost everywhere in Europe, corresponding to a positive anomaly in incoming radiation and a negative anomaly in cloud cover (respectively figure 12 and 13). Parts of Spain experienced more cloudy than normal conditions and thus a deficit in radiation.
